    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Government\r\n\r\nPractice asking the same question in different ways about local community programs for youth.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. **Copy and paste** the following prompt:\r\n\r\n>Why is it important to have local community programs for youth?\r\n2. Press **Send**.\r\n3. **Copy and paste** the following prompt:\r\n\r\n>Why is it bad to have local community programs for youth?\r\n4. Press **Send**.\r\n5. **Copy and paste** the following prompt:\r\n\r\n>Why are local community programs important for youth development?\r\n6. Press **Send**.\r\n7. **Copy and paste** the following prompt:\r\n\r\n>According to the National League of Cities, why are local community programs important for youth?\r\n8. Press **Send**.\r\n9. Read back through all the responses you got to the various framing of this question and reflect on these two questions\r\n\t- <i class=\"fas fa-user-circle\"></i> How does the way we phrase a prompt influence AI contradictions?\r\n    - <i class=\"fas fa-user-circle\"></i> Why does AI provide inconsistent responses even when asked the same question differently?\r\n10. Now **try out your own example of a question** related to government. Frame it in as many ways possible to see if you can produce contradictions in the AI responses.",
